WorkItem.Description:
Static generic methods don't seem to be supported. This would be an incredibly useful feature to me.

```
//Compiles fine
class MyClass {
    myGenericMethod<U>(input: U): void { }
}

//Compiles fine
class MyGenericClass<T> {
    myGenericMethod<U>(input: U): void { }
}

//Does not compile
class MyStaticClass {
    static myGenericMethod<U>(input: U): void { }
}

//Does not compile
class MyStaticGenericClass<T> {
    static myGenericMethod<U>(input: U): void { }
}
```

Unrelated to the issue, but you fixed one of my other issues. How can I install the latest build of TypeScript 0.9 alpha? I'd love to get my hands on the most recent changes.

Best,
Doug Rubino
